DNS resolution
        Is the process of translating IP addresses to domain names.

Encrypted traffic:
        Network traffic is encrypted with SSL certificates before going out to the Internet.

traffic goes through a firewall:
        Traffic passes through the firewall to monitor incoming and outgoing network traffic and decides whether
        to allow or block specific traffic based on a defined set of security rules.

that the request is distributed via a load balancer:
        The requests made to the network are distributed by the load balancer so as not to saturate the servers.

that the web server answers the request by serving a web page:

that the application server generates the web page:

that the application server request data from the database:

